Package: anonsurf
Architecture: any
Priority: optional
Depends: bash (>= 5.0), iptables, tor, libc6, nyx, systemd | systemctl, sudo, bleachbit
Recommends: libnotify-bin, i2p, onioncircuits, connect-proxy, onionshare, torsocks, tor-geoipdb, parrot-menu
Suggests: gnunet-gtk, gnunet, vidalia
Description: Anonymization toolkit for Parrot Security OS
 AnonSurf is an anonymization toolkit that applies configurations and toolkits
 to prevent tracking and surveillance on end-user. AnonSurf create a Tor
 transparent proxy and use iptables to forward all traffic through Tor
 network. It also disables IPv6, clear applications's cache to prevent
 data leak.

Package: anonsurf-gtk
Architecture: any
Priority: optional
Depends: anonsurf, libc6
Description: Anonymization toolkit for Parrot Security OS
 This package contains AnonSurf's graphic user interface
 and its menu's launcher which was written in Nim and
 gintro library (a binding of GTK framework).
